{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"sulky-pane-flag","description":"## Reproduction Steps\n1. Run `rebar review-plan <epic>` on an epic with N children (observed N=8).\n2. The review runs >25 min with no completion (appears hung).\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- Expected: epic review completes in a few minutes.\n- Actual: ~2*N sequential agentic LLM calls (~75-150s each) ⇒ ~27 min for N=8.\n\n## Root cause (PROVEN, runtime evidence)\nContainer criteria G3/G4 (`container_only`, levels=[epic,story]) run in a SEQUENTIAL\ndouble loop `for crit in [G3,G4]: for child in children: pass1_container(...)` at\n`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/pass1.py:62-101`, executed OUTSIDE the ThreadPoolExecutor that\nparallelizes every other tier (`pass1.py:246-273`). Each `pass1_container` is an agentic\ncall (bounded by request_limit=ceil(max_iterations/2)). Faulthandler + per-pairing\ninstrumentation showed pairings completing one-by-one at 73-146s each, progressing through\nchildren — bounded-but-slow, NOT an infinite loop. Amplifier: the budget cap scales UP with\nchild count (`sizing.py` centrality), so shedding never engages for large epics.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The container fan-out is parallelized (submit the 2*N pairings into the existing\n      ThreadPoolExecutor) OR otherwise bounded so an epic review completes in minutes.\n- [ ] The budget cap no longer disables shedding as child count grows (decouple the container\n      term from centrality).\n- [ ] An 8-child epic review completes within a few minutes (regression test / measured).","id":"c81c-cbcd-17a0-43d2","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"plan-review container fan-out (G3/G4) is sequential — epic review wall-time ~2*N_children agentic calls, looks like a hang"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782535505203944001,"uuid":"b9f4f110-4377-4a39-bcd5-fface452687a"}